The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Captains conclave
Mumbai: A one-day conclave of Ranji Trophy captains and coaches of all the zones would be held here on June 4, according to sources in the Board of Control for Cricket in India (BCCI). The conclave has been convened to discuss the conduct of various domestic tournaments last season and elicit suggestions from the participants for any further improvement. Former India captain Polly Umrigar, recently came against inclusion of a foreign team in the Duleep Trophy.  (PTI)  Copyright 
